Scatterplot of hashrate of regional Data

library(ggplot2)

df <- read.csv("Regional harshrate global 1.csv")
df$date <- as.Date(df$date)

df <- df %>%
  mutate(year = lubridate::year(date),  
         month = lubridate::month(date))

countries <- unique(df$country)
plot_list <- lapply(countries, function(country) {
  country_df <- df %>% filter(country == !!country)
  p <- ggplot(country_df, aes(x = as.Date(paste(year, month, "01", sep = "-")), y = monthly_absolute_hashrate_EH.S)) +
    geom_line(color = "blue") +
    geom_point(shape = 21, color = "black", fill = "red", size = 1) +
    labs(x = "Date", y = "Hashrate") +
    theme_minimal()
    
  p <- p + ggtitle(paste("Bit_Hashrate", country))
  p <- p + theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 8))  
  p <- p + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 5, angle=90))
  
  return(p)
})

print(plot_list)

library(hrbrthemes)

##       if Arial Narrow is not on your system, please see https://bit.ly/arialnarrow
library(viridis)
## Loading required package: viridisLite
df <- df %>%
  mutate(year = lubridate::year(date),  
         month = lubridate::month(date))

# Summarize the data by country and year
summary_df <- df %>%
  group_by(country, year) %>%
  summarise(n = sum(monthly_absolute_hashrate_EH.S))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'country'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
countries <- unique(summary_df$country)

summary_df %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = n, group = country, color = country)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE) +
  ggtitle("Bit_Hashrate") +
  theme_ipsum() +
  ylab("Hashrate")

Hypothesis test - Anova test

Null hypothesis: H0: In the United States, China, and other countries, as Bitcoin transaction volume increases, hashrate and carbon dioxide emissions will increase equally.

Alternative hypothesis: H1:

The United States, China, and other countries will not all have the same hashrate and average carbon dioxide emissions. The p-value is 0.0008, which is < α. *(0.05). So we can reject H0 The alternative hypothesis is supported at the 95% significance level.

library(ezids)
